The Px4 is built around a modular concept so these pistols can be adapted to different needs. The Px4 features an exclusive, Beretta-designed locked breech with rotating barrel system, reducing felt recoil and muzzle rise. Chrome-lined barrels provide extreme corrosion resistance, as well as ease of cleaning and feature a deeply recessed combat muzzle crown to protect the rifling. The light frame employs a durable fiberglass-reinforced polymer with a milstd-1913 picatinny rail and a modular grip system for a custom fit. The Bruniton non-reflective black coating is offer superior resistance against corrosion and wear The Px4 Storm is a semi-automatic pistol manufactured in Italy and intended for personal defense and law enforcement deployment. The Beretta Px4 Storm is hybrid design borrowing the short-recoil, rotating barrel as the Beretta 8000 models and the trigger and safety system from the 92, 96, and M9 series. What makes the Beretta Px4 Storm unique is the light-weight polymer construction with steel inserts, a modular trigger group, fully enclosing slide, Picatinny rail, and changeable backstrap options. The Beretta Px4 Storm can fire 9x19mm Parabellum, .40 S&W, and .45 ACP rounds.Design Specifications• Weight: 27.7 OZ (without magazine)• Length: 7.55 in• Barrel Length: 4.0 inInterchangeable PartsBeing one of the most versatile Beretta pistols available, the Px4 Storm has a number of parts that are designed to be removable and interchangeable. The back strap, magazine release button, slide catch, and hammer unit mechanism are all interchangeable with a variety of options. The back strap comes in slim, standard and oversized varieties. The magazine button can be mounted on either sides and be replaced by large or combat (extended) sized options. To avoid snagging the pistol when the weapon is drawn quickly, the slide catch can be replaced with a slimmer version. The Beretta Px4 Storm is currently used by a variety of military and law enforcement organizations including the Buenos Aires Metropolitan Police, the Canada Border Services Agency, the Maryland State Police, Venezuelan National Guard, and the South African Police Service.

title: For Sale:  Custom 16" DD M4 AR15 Rifle with all the bells and whistles
postcontent:
I'm taking a job in Hawaii, so I've decided to sell my lovingly assembled AR15 rifle and AR pistol to raise funds for the move (I'll have a good job when I get over there and will rebuild!)
Details: Rifle:
Album: http://imgur.com/a/3izpm#0
Aero Precision lower with SAA-installed LPK with m4 commercial buffer tube collapsible stock. Magpul bad lever, Magpul oversize trigger guard (poly) and anti walk hammer/trigger pins installed by me.
Aero precision a4 upper with Nickel boron auto BCG, matech US Army surplus Rear sight, Magpul PTS front sight, fully cowitnessed with Aimpoint 7000SC red dot, UTG machined aluminum high-profile QD mount (has held Sub MOA Zero going on 3 years now through about 500 rds). Aluminum VFG and UTG bipod (connects with a QD rail to bipod connection). Ambi-oversized charging handle. Blackhawk! 2 point sling
Daniel defense chrome-lined, polygonal rifled 1:7 5.56/.223 M4 profile barrel with mid length gas system. YHM low profile gas block, rifle length aluminum free float quad rail. YHM phantom comp/flash hider.
This particular build was built mid 2012 and all the parts reflect that stylistically. this was my fifth build and it was flawlessly put together. A torque wrench was used to tighten the barrel nut to 65 foot lbs, all screws installed with blue locktite.
This rifle has been used at the range and has minor scuffs from transport and range use. It is sub MOA accurate, and I can reliably hit a steel target standing/sitting at 200 yards with no professional training. It's a phenomenal rifle for someone who wants a ready-to-go package. A long range optic turns it into an SPR, essentially.
I've put about 1500 into it (not counting panic markup on some components. 500-600 rounds through it. Appx 9.5 lbs as configured. It will reliably eat anything. I've shot practically all brands through it without a single malfunction, save for a couple double-feeds from a piece of shit aluminum magazine that I threw away. All accessories are QD.
I'm asking $1000. Price is firm. This is a ready-to-go rig and requires no adjustments to start schooling your buddies at the range. Currently zero is set to 150 yards.

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  AAC Made 300 Blackout Barrel
postcontent: This Advanced Armament Co (AAC) AR-15 Barrel Assembly is perfect for the shooter who wishes to build or convert an AR-15 to chamber the new 300 AAC Blackout round in order to take advantage of its unique ballistic characteristics. The barrel is finished inside and out with a highly durable and corrosion resistant Black Nitride, a treatment that produces an extremely hard, slick surface on the steel that resists carbon adhesion for easier cleaning and maintenance. The Nitride process converts the steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered with it due to the uneven application of chrome inside a barrel's bore.  This 16" barrel features a 1 in 7" twist and is threaded 5/8"-24 at the muzzle for easy installation of flash hiders, muzzle brakes, and/or sound suppressors. It utilizes the versatile carbine length gas system, a good choice for this cartridge if various weights and types of ammunition are to be used. Most subsonic and supersonic loads, fired from either a suppressed or unsuppressed gun, are compatible with this configuration. However, some subsonic ammunition may not always cycle reliably under adverse conditions or in a severely fouled firearm without a sound suppressor attached to provide extra backpressure. Barrel assembly includes a carbine gas tube, low profile steel gas block, barrel extension and locator pin. Also includes a AAC Blackout 51 tooth Flash Hider for Flash Suppression or Quick attach/ detach of AAC suppressors. A $105.00 value.  Requires barrel nut for installation (not included).
